  "issue_number": 823,
  "issue_title": "[Bug]:`MinerEvaluationCache` doesn't strip mirror file contents \u2014 unbounded memory growth",
  "issue_body": "## Problem\n\n`MinerEvaluationCache.store()` drops `patch` strings from legacy PRs (via `_pr_for_cache`), but the equivalent mirror lists (`mirror_merged_prs`, `mirror_open_prs`, `mirror_closed_prs`) are stored as-is. The `head_content` and `base_content` blobs on `ScoredMirrorPR.files` \u2014 whole head/base file contents fetched from the mirror \u2014 stay in memory for the lifetime of the cached entry.\n\n## Where\n\n`gittensor/classes.py` \u2014 `MinerEvaluationCache._build_cache_entry` only iterates the legacy `*_pull_requests` lists. The three `mirror_*_prs` lists fall through `copy.copy(evaluation)` as shared references, so nothing strips their file payloads.\n\n## Impact\n\n- Cached evaluations grow with every mirror-scored PR and never shrink.\n- Worst on validators scoring high-traffic mirror-enabled repos with large diffs (one big PR can pin multiple MB).\n- The cache is per-UID and survives across rounds, so the leak compounds the longer the validator runs.\n\n## Expected\n\nAfter `cache.store(evaluation)`:\n\n- Every `ScoredMirrorPR.files` on the cached copy is `None` (or each `MirrorFile.head_content` / `base_content` is `None`) across all three mirror buckets.\n- The original `evaluation` passed in is untouched \u2014 DB storage downstream still needs the full file payloads.\n- Legacy `FileChange.patch` stripping behavior is unchanged.\n\n## Repro\n\n1. Run a validator against a repo with `mirror_enabled: true` in `master_repositories.json`.\n2. Score a miner that has at least one non-trivial mirror PR on that repo.\n3. Inspect `validator.evaluation_cache._cache[uid].evaluation.mirror_merged_prs[0].files[0].head_content` \u2014 still populated with the full file contents.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-01T20:56:28.000Z",
  "test_cmd": [
